race.comment: BANGALOW ROAD (8) was comfortably accounted for when third last time out over 1335m at Geelong, beaten 3.5 lengths after being prominent at the turn. That followed a win at Kilmore at the previous outing. Looks well-placed in this race, though, and there's no reason she cannot make amends. ERMINIA (9) resumed four weeks ago over 1100m at St Arnaud and was only beaten 1.75 lengths into fourth. The engagement of Linda Meech is noteworthy. Strips fitter and can figure in the finish. GRASSMERE JEWEL (1) has a massive weight for a mare - 65.5kg - but that's because she's dropping sharply in grade on recent assignments and she'd give it a shake at her best. HUGHIE (5) has been racing consistently in races of similar quality to this but has a tricky gate to overcome. PORT LOUIS (7) did little and finished 4.5 lengths from the winner in ninth over 1107m at Geelong last start but is good enough at his best.
